Hey I'm usually not a bleeding heart type but this story bothers me, especially reading these comments. As the parent of a 14 year old girl I can tell you that this girl is not any dumber than any other kid. Girls that age are unpredictable even to themselves with their body and mind changing every day. Their brain is not fully developed and they can't foresee the outcomes of situations. So she did a dumb thing, ok. But who among you never did something dumb or risky when you were a teenager? My condolences go to her parents and I'm saddened to hear of her death. She was just a child trying to become a woman and something was missing in her life. It's really sad.
